---
import BaseLayout from '~/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Ornament from '~/components/ui/Ornament.astro';
import Card from '~/components/ui/Card.astro';
import { Image } from 'astro:assets';
import commodorePhoto from '~/assets/members/commodore-hero.png';
import rodPhoto from '~/assets/members/rod-captain.png';
import mackPhoto from '~/assets/members/fairymack-captain.png';
import mikePhoto from '~/assets/members/mike-captain.png';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="About the Club"
  description="The Founding, the Fleet, and the Commodore. Miccosukee Yacht Club — constituted MMXXV, Miccosukee Land Coop, Florida."
  active="about"
>

  <!-- Page header -->
  <section class="page-header">
    <div class="container">
      <img src="/assets/compass-rose.svg" alt="" width="100" height="100" class="page-compass" />
      <span class="eyebrow-rule">Concerning the Club</span>
      <h1>The Founding, the Fleet, the Commodore</h1>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Founding narrative -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="narrow">
      <p class="lead" style="text-align: center; margin-bottom: var(--space-7);">
        The Miccosukee Yacht Club was constituted in the year of our reckoning Two Thousand and
        Twenty-Six, in consequence of a remark made over an iced beverage, which the present
        Commodore took rather more seriously than was perhaps intended.
      </p>

      <h2 id="founding">Article I &mdash; The Founding</h2>
      <p>
        What began as a passing jest among friends has, by deliberate action and the procurement of
        this very digital quarter, become a private nautical society. The Club takes its name from
        the Miccosukee Land Cooperative, where several members reside &mdash; one of Florida's
        oldest intentional communities, established in 1973 on 344 acres of northeastern Leon County.
        The Coop is named after the small town of Miccosukee. So is the lake nearby. The roads
        inside the Coop are named after Beatles songs. The Club has not yet held a meeting on
        Abbey Road, but considers this a future agenda item.
      </p>
      <p>
        There is a lake on the property. It is shallow, heavily vegetated, and unsuitable for
        any vessel drawing more than a kayak paddle. The Club has accepted this gracefully and
        sails elsewhere, returning home to a community of friends in the country who are largely
        unbothered by the whole arrangement.
      </p>
      <p>
        The Club admits members on the invitation of the Membership Committee, accepts no fees
        from anyone &mdash; but reserves the right to do both at any time.
      </p>

      <h2 id="fleet" style="margin-top: var(--space-8);">Article II &mdash; The Fleet</h2>
      <p>
        The Club's flagship is the <em>S/V Nomine Carens</em>, a 2007 Catalina 309 sloop
        owned and captained by Rod Joly, berthed in Carrabelle. She is the more impressive
        of the two vessels by a considerable margin: a proper sail-driven yacht with a diesel
        auxiliary, a fin keel, and accommodations sufficient for a long weekend at sea.
        Her permanent name remains before the Naming Committee. The Committee has not yet convened.
        In fact, there is no Naming Committee. One should be formed.
      </p>
      <p>
        The Club's second vessel is the <em>M.V. Porkchop Express</em>, a 2023 Sun Tracker
        Party Barge with a Mercury 150 outboard, operated by Captain Harris. She is native to
        the St. Marks River and enjoys the more leisurely pace of Lake Talquin in the cooler
        months, where she can be found anchored near the shoreline in the shade of oaks and
        pines, with FSU football on the radio. She is also known to brave the salt on occasion
        and make the run out to the K-Tower sand bar for a day of sea life, light sport fishing,
        and the hosting of myriad drunken sailors. She has the larger share of the Club's
        logged hours by virtue of being towable to any boat ramp within a tank of fuel.
      </p>
      <p>
        Both vessels are maintained under individual ownership. The Club does not hold title to
        either vessel and is not responsible for their insurance, storage, or the inevitable small
        repairs that follow any outing of consequence. Captain Harris performs the maintenance
        on the <em>Porkchop Express</em> single-handed. The <em>Nomine Carens</em> is worked on
        as a team, which is the proper way to work on a sailboat and, in the Club's experience,
        the only way to work on a sailboat that ever finishes.
      </p>

      <Ornament />

      <h2 id="commodore">Article III &mdash; The Commodore</h2>
      <p>
        The office of Commodore is currently held by J. B. Harris, who appointed himself to the
        position at the founding and has not been seriously challenged. The incumbent retains
        office until a member in good standing issues a formal challenge. Challenges are settled
        by a single hand of high-stakes Texas Hold 'em. At the challenger's election, a
        sword-fight to the death may be substituted. The Club does not own swords.
      </p>
      <p>
        The Commodore is responsible for the calendar, the flag, and the general dignity of the
        proceedings. He does not have additional authority in matters not covered by these Articles.
        The Articles do not cover most matters. This has not been a problem.
      </p>

      <Ornament />

      <h2 id="membership">Article IV &mdash; The Membership</h2>
      <p>
        The Club presently numbers four members in good standing, each accompanied by a first
        mate of considerably better judgment:
      </p>

      <div class="roster">
        <div class="roster-entry roster-entry-photo">
          <Image src={commodorePhoto} alt="J. B. Harris, Commodore" width={480} densities={[1, 2]} format="webp" quality={72} class="roster-photo" />
          <div class="roster-entry-text">
            <div class="roster-name">J. B. Harris</div>
            <div class="roster-title">Commodore &middot; Captain, <em>M.V. Porkchop Express</em></div>
            <div class="roster-mate">First Mate: Melanie</div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="roster-entry roster-entry-photo">
          <Image src={rodPhoto} alt="Rod Joly at the helm" width={480} densities={[1, 2]} format="webp" quality={72} class="roster-photo" style="object-position: 62% 8%;" />
          <div class="roster-entry-text">
            <div class="roster-name">Rod Joly</div>
            <div class="roster-title">Captain, <em>S/V Nomine Carens</em></div>
            <div class="roster-mate">First Mate: Michelle</div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="roster-entry roster-entry-photo">
          <Image src={mackPhoto} alt="Fairy Mack Lane" width={480} densities={[1, 2]} format="webp" quality={72} class="roster-photo" style="object-position: center 20%;" />
          <div class="roster-entry-text">
            <div class="roster-name">"Fairy" Mack Lane</div>
            <div class="roster-title">Member in Good Standing</div>
            <div class="roster-mate">First Mate: Cassie</div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="roster-entry roster-entry-photo">
          <Image src={mikePhoto} alt="Mike Humelsine" width={480} densities={[1, 2]} format="webp" quality={72} class="roster-photo" style="object-position: center 15%;" />
          <div class="roster-entry-text">
            <div class="roster-name">Mike Humelsine</div>
            <div class="roster-title">Member in Good Standing</div>
            <div class="roster-mate">First Mate: Chelsea</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p style="margin-top: var(--space-6);">
        The Club's culture centers on good beer, fine cigars, semi-honest stories, and the company
        of people who know when to be quiet on the water. Spouses and first mates are considered
        full participants in all Club activities and substantially better at reading charts.
      </p>

      <div class="signature-block">
        <span class="script-sig">&mdash; J. B. Harris, Commodore</span>
        <div class="signature-title">Founding Member &middot; Anno I &middot; Self-Appointed</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Stats -->
  <section class="section section-paper">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="stats-grid">
        <Card>
          <div class="stat-number">IV</div>
          <div class="stat-label">Members in good standing</div>
        </Card>
        <Card>
          <div class="stat-number">II</div>
          <div class="stat-label">Vessels in the fleet</div>
        </Card>
        <Card>
          <div class="stat-number">MMXXV</div>
          <div class="stat-label">Year of constitution</div>
        </Card>
        <Card>
          <div class="stat-number">0</div>
          <div class="stat-label">Circumnavigations attempted</div>
        </Card>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Signal flags decoration -->
  <section class="section section-deep flags-section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="flags-inner">
        <img src="/assets/signal-flags.svg" alt="International signal flags" class="flags-img" />
        <div class="flags-caption">
          <span class="eyebrow-rule" style="color: var(--brass-200);">The Signal Flags</span>
          <p style="color: var(--fg-on-deep-muted); font-style: italic; margin-top: var(--space-3); max-width: 42ch;">
            The Club maintains a full set of International Code of Signals flags, sufficient for all
            occasions of ceremony and several of mild alarm.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</BaseLayout>

<style>
.page-header {
  background: var(--bg-deep);
  color: var(--fg-on-deep);
  text-align: center;
  padding-block: var(--space-10) var(--space-8);
}
.page-compass {
  margin-inline: auto;
  margin-bottom: var(--space-5);
  opacity: 0.8;
}
.page-header .eyebrow-rule { color: var(--brass-200); }
.page-header .eyebrow-rule::before, .page-header .eyebrow-rule::after { background: var(--brass-500); }
.page-header h1 {
  color: var(--sail-50);
  margin-top: var(--space-4);
  font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, var(--fs-h1));
}

.roster {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
  gap: var(--space-5);
  margin-top: var(--space-5);
}
.roster-entry {
  background: var(--bg-card);
  border: 1px solid var(--border);
  border-top: 3px solid var(--brass-500);
  padding: var(--space-5);
}
.roster-entry-photo {
  padding: 0;
  overflow: hidden;
}
.roster-photo {
  width: 100%;
  height: 200px;
  object-fit: cover;
  object-position: center top;
  display: block;
}
.roster-entry-text {
  padding: var(--space-5);
}
.roster-name {
  font-family: var(--font-display);
  font-size: var(--fs-h5);
  font-weight: 500;
  color: var(--fg);
}
.roster-title {
  font-family: var(--font-serif);
  font-size: 13px;
  color: var(--fg-muted);
  margin-top: 4px;
  line-height: 1.5;
}
.roster-mate {
  font-family: var(--font-sans);
  font-size: 11px;
  font-weight: 600;
  letter-spacing: var(--tracking-wide);
  text-transform: uppercase;
  color: var(--brass-600);
  margin-top: var(--space-3);
}

.signature-block { margin-top: var(--space-7); }
.signature-title {
  font-family: var(--font-sans);
  font-size: 11px;
  font-weight: 600;
  letter-spacing: var(--tracking-xwide);
  text-transform: uppercase;
  color: var(--brass-600);
  margin-top: var(--space-2);
}

.stats-grid {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr);
  gap: var(--space-5);
  text-align: center;
}
.stat-number {
  font-family: var(--font-display);
  font-size: 64px;
  font-weight: 500;
  color: var(--brass-500);
  line-height: 1;
}
.stat-label {
  font-family: var(--font-sans);
  font-size: 12px;
  font-weight: 600;
  letter-spacing: var(--tracking-wide);
  text-transform: uppercase;
  color: var(--fg-muted);
  margin-top: var(--space-3);
}

.flags-section { padding-block: var(--space-8); }
.flags-inner {
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  gap: var(--space-8);
  flex-wrap: wrap;
}
.flags-img {
  max-height: 120px;
  opacity: 0.7;
  filter: brightness(1.2) sepia(0.2);
}
.flags-caption .eyebrow-rule::before,
.flags-caption .eyebrow-rule::after { background: var(--brass-500); }

@media (max-width: 900px) {
  .stats-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; }
}
@media (max-width: 600px) {
  .stats-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; }
  .roster { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  .flags-inner { flex-direction: column; text-align: center; }
}
</style>
